This directory contains some useful tools for the 
hikey development workflow

bluetooth.sh -  a useful host script for pairing bluetooth devices
                such as remote controls and keyboards

adb.sh -    a device script to setup adb over tcp. 
            Useful if you're using any external usb devices given
            the hikey's USB hardware limitations

debugir.sh -    a device script to enable ir debugging and setup
                rc-5 and rc-6 protocols, ir-keytable required see
                https://github.com/trevd/android_external_keytable